# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODEOWNERS — ProxyShield
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub automatically requests review from these owners on every PR that
# touches the matching paths.  At least ONE owner must approve before merge.
#
# Format:  <path-pattern>   <@user-or-team> [<@user-or-team> ...]
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default — every file requires review from the core team.
*                           @KidCarmi

# ── Security-critical files — require explicit security review ──────────────
# Any change to authentication, TLS, or proxy core requires security sign-off.
auth.go                     @KidCarmi
auth_ldap.go                @KidCarmi
auth_oidc.go                @KidCarmi
ca.go                       @KidCarmi
tls.go                      @KidCarmi
proxy.go                    @KidCarmi
security.go                 @KidCarmi
geoip.go                    @KidCarmi

# ── Policy engine — changes affect all traffic decisions ────────────────────
policy.go                   @KidCarmi
store.go                    @KidCarmi

# ── CI / Release pipeline — changes here affect all deployments ─────────────
.github/                    @KidCarmi
Dockerfile                  @KidCarmi
install.sh                  @KidCarmi

# ── Configuration schema — breaking changes need special care ───────────────
config.go                   @KidCarmi
config.yaml                 @KidCarmi
config.example.yaml         @KidCarmi

# ── Frontend — UI changes need UX + security review (XSS risk) ─────────────
static/                     @KidCarmi
ui.go                       @KidCarmi
